03/02/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- Defence Minister Vecdi Gonul said Monday (2 February) that his government has proposed designating local companies to repair US armoured vehicles in Iraq. Currently, the damaged vehicles are being sent back to the United States for work.
In other news, German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder will arrive on a three-day official visit to Turkey on 22 February. He is to meet with President Ahmet Necdet Sezer and Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan. (Anadolu Agency, TRT 2 - 02/02/04)
